{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870328416,"sessionID":"ses_285e24e54ffeE9wMSq27VFW3fQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1dec12001JLtdrwHXkNuYlB","messageID":"msg_d7a1dc056001vc8febzo1E06qS","sessionID":"ses_285e24e54ffeE9wMSq27VFW3fQ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_3ed74dd39bc545c7913ab2ea","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-029 ŌĆö SDK HTTP Õ║ĢÕ▒éÕ«óµłĘń½»\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec supplements the base `python-sdk/spec.md` with additional acceptance scenarios focused on the HTTPÕ║ĢÕ▒éÕ«óµłĘń½» (HTTP underlying client) implementation for AR-029.\n\n**AR:** AR-029  \n**Module:** sdk-python  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: HTTP Session ńö¤ÕæĮÕæ©µ£¤ń«ĪńÉå\n\nThe system SHALL manage `requests.Session` lifecycle to ensure proper connection pooling and cleanup.\n\n### Scenario: Session creation with connection pooling\n\n- **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)` is called\n- **WHEN** the function executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` mounted for both `http://` and `https://` schemes\n- **AND** the adapter SHALL have `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10`\n\n### Scenario: Session context manager cleanup\n\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` or `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** the `with` block exits normally\n- **THEN** the underlying `requests.Session` SHALL be closed via `.close()`\n- **AND** all HTTP connections SHALL be released back to the pool\n\n### Scenario: Session cleanup on exception\n\n- **GIVEN** an exception occurs within a context manager block\n- **WHEN** the `__exit__` method is called with exception info\n- **THEN** the session SHALL still be closed\n- **AND** the original exception SHALL be re-raised after cleanup\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: HTTP Ķ»Ęµ▒éĶČģµŚČĶĪīõĖ║\n\nThe system SHALL handle connect timeouts and read timeouts correctly for all HTTP operations.\n\n### Scenario: Connect timeout applies to all requests\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized with `connect_timeout=5.0`\n- **WHEN** a request is made to an unreachable host\n- **THEN** a `requests.exceptions.ConnectTimeout` SHALL be raised within 5 seconds\n\n### Scenario: Read timeout for long-running operations\n\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with a command that takes longer than the read timeout\n- **WHEN** the server does not respond within `(connect_timeout + timeout)` seconds\n- **THEN** a `requests.exceptions.ReadTimeout` SHALL be raised\n\n### Scenario: Timeout tuple construction\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke` is called with default timeout settings\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the `timeout` parameter SHALL be a tuple `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `connect_timeout` defaults to `5.0` and `timeout` defaults to `120`\n\n### Scenario: Per-call timeout override\n\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=300)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the read timeout SHALL be `timeout + 2.0` seconds (302 seconds total) to allow for server-side timeout handling\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: HTTP Õż┤ķā©ń«ĪńÉå\n\nThe system SHALL correctly set and manage HTTP headers for both control plane and data plane requests.\n\n### Scenario: Authorization header on control plane\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized with a valid `auth_token`\n- **WHEN** `create_session` is called\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include header `Authorization: Bearer {auth_token}`\n\n### Scenario: No Authorization header when token is empty\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without `auth_token`\n- **WHEN** a request is made\n- **THEN** the `Authorization` header SHALL NOT be included\n\n### Scenario: Session ID header for Code Interpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `session_id=\"test-session-123\"`\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` is called\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: test-session-123`\n\n### Scenario: Session ID header for Agent Runtime\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is used\n- **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include header defined by `SESSION_HEADER` constant (`x-agentcube-session-id`)\n\n### Scenario: Content-Type header for JSON requests\n\n- **GIVEN** `_request` is called with a JSON body\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the header `Content-Type: application/json` SHALL be set\n\n### Scenario: Multipart upload content-type\n\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent as multipart/form-data\n- **THEN** the outer request SHALL NOT have `Content-Type: application/json`\n- **AND** the `x-agentcube-session-id` header SHALL still be included\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: HTTP ķöÖĶ»»ÕżäńÉå\n\nThe system SHALL handle HTTP error responses appropriately and convert them to SDK-specific exceptions.\n\n### Scenario: Non-200 response on create session\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session` receives HTTP 400 or 500\n- **WHEN** the response is not successful\n- **THEN** an appropriate `requests.exceptions.HTTPError` SHALL be raised\n\n### Scenario: 404 treated as success for delete\n\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session` is called with a non-existent `session_id`\n- **WHEN** the server returns HTTP 404\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (treating \"not found\" as successful deletion)\n\n### Scenario: Connection error handling\n\n- **GIVEN** the Router is unreachable\n- **WHEN** a data plane request is made\n- **THEN** a `requests.exceptions.ConnectionError` SHALL be raised\n\n### Scenario: Response JSON parsing failure\n\n- **GIVEN** the server returns non-JSON response\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` tries to parse the response as JSON\n- **THEN** a `JSONDecodeError` or equivalent SHALL be raised\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Base URL Ķ¦Żµ×ÉõĖÄµ×äķĆĀ\n\nThe system SHALL correctly resolve and construct base URLs for both control plane and data plane.\n\n### Scenario: Control plane URL from environment\n\n- **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable is set to `https://wm.example.com`\n- **AND** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without arguments\n- **WHEN** the client is used\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `https://wm.example.com`\n\n### Scenario: Control plane URL from argument\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"https://custom-wm.example.com\")`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** argument SHALL take precedence over environment variable\n\n### Scenario: Data plane base URL from router\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `router_url`, `namespace`, and `cr_name`\n- **AND** `base_url` is NOT provided\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be constructed as `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")`\n\n### Scenario: Data plane base URL explicit override\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is initialized with explicit `base_url=\"https://custom.example.com/api\"`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be exactly `https://custom.example.com/api`\n\n### Scenario: Agent Runtime base URL construction\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `router_url`, `namespace`, and `agent_name`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Ķ»Ęµ▒éõĮōµ×äķĆĀ\n\nThe system SHALL construct HTTP request bodies correctly for different operation types.\n\n### Scenario: Execute command JSON body\n\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with `command=[\"echo\", \"hello\"]` and `timeout=60`\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the JSON body SHALL be `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello\"], \"timeout\": \"60s\"}`\n\n### Scenario: Write file base64 encoding\n\n- **GIVEN** `write_file` is called with `content=\"Hello World\"` and `remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\"`\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the JSON body SHALL include `{\"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"content\": \"<base64-encoded>\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n\n### Scenario: Download file streaming\n\n- **GIVEN** `download_file` is called\n- **WHEN** the GET request is made to `api/files/{clean_path}`\n- **THEN** `stream=True` SHALL be set on the request\n\n### Scenario: List files query parameter\n\n- **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\"/tmp\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the request SHALL be GET to `api/files` with query parameter `path=/tmp`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Token µ¢ćõ╗ČĶ»╗ÕÅ¢\n\nThe system SHALL handle token file reading gracefully with appropriate fallback behavior.\n\n### Scenario: Token file exists and readable\n\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` exists with content `eyJ...`\n- **AND** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without `auth_token`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `self.token` SHALL be the file contents (stripped)\n\n### Scenario: Token file does not exist\n\n- **GIVEN** the service account token file does not exist\n- **AND** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without `auth_token`\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return an empty string `\"\"`\n- **AND** no exception SHALL be raised\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: µŚźÕ┐ŚĶ«░ÕĮĢ\n\nThe system SHALL log HTTP operations for debugging and monitoring purposes.\n\n### Scenario: Logger creation with default level\n\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the default log level SHALL be `logging.INFO`\n\n### Scenario: Custom logger level\n\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube\", level=logging.DEBUG)` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is configured\n- **THEN** the logger level SHALL be `logging.DEBUG`\n\n### Scenario: Verbose mode enables debug logging\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=True)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the client is created\n- **THEN** the logger SHALL be set to `DEBUG` level\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Õ«óµłĘń½»ÕŁŚµ«ĄÕłØÕ¦ŗÕī¢\n\nThe system SHALL correctly initialize all client fields as documented.\n\n### Scenario: CodeInterpreterClient fields\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(name=\"test\", namespace=\"ns\", ttl=1800, verbose=True, session_id=\"sess-1\")`\n- **WHEN** the client is initialized\n- **THEN** the instance SHALL have fields: `name=\"test\"`, `namespace=\"ns\"`, `ttl=1800`, `verbose=True`, `session_id=\"sess-1\"`, `cp_client`, `dp_client`, `router_url`, `logger`\n\n### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient fields\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"agent1\", namespace=\"default\", timeout=60, connect_timeout=3.0)`\n- **WHEN** the client is initialized\n- **THEN** the instance SHALL have fields: `agent_name=\"agent1\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `timeout=60`, `connect_timeout=3.0`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`, `logger`\n\n### Scenario: ControlPlaneClient defaults\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is initialized with no arguments\n- **WHEN** the client is created\n- **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120`, `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`, `self.pool_connections` SHALL be `10`, `self.pool_maxsize` SHALL be `10`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Õ╝éÕĖĖń▒╗Õ▒éµ¼Īń╗ōµ×ä\n\nThe system SHALL provide a clear exception hierarchy for different error conditions.\n\n### Scenario: AgentCubeError is base class\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentCubeError` is the base exception\n- **WHEN** any SDK-specific exception is raised\n- **THEN** it SHALL be a subclass of `AgentCubeError`\n\n### Scenario: CommandExecutionError attributes\n\n- **GIVEN** `CommandExecutionError` is raised for a failed command\n- **WHEN** the exception is caught\n- **THEN** it SHALL have `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command` attributes\n- **AND** the exception message SHALL include the exit code and stderr\n\n### Scenario: SessionError definition exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `SessionError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n- **WHEN** the module is imported\n- **THEN** `SessionError` SHALL be available as `AgentCubeError` subclass\n\n### Scenario: DataPlaneError definition exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `DataPlaneError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n- **WHEN** the module is imported\n- **THEN** `DataPlaneError` SHALL be available as `AgentCubeError` subclass","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775870328402,"end":1775870328411}}}}
