{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775870357696,"sessionID":"ses_285e24e54ffeE9wMSq27VFW3fQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1f30bf001evXLSiHog4JPCK","messageID":"msg_d7a1f297e001V3JT9q3faHgiYD","sessionID":"ses_285e24e54ffeE9wMSq27VFW3fQ","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870423937,"sessionID":"ses_285e24e54ffeE9wMSq27VFW3fQ","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1f36ff001sUseZQO4K30m2B","messageID":"msg_d7a1f297e001V3JT9q3faHgiYD","sessionID":"ses_285e24e54ffeE9wMSq27VFW3fQ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_5a67fa8d621f40cdbc199f40","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-029 ŌĆö SDK HTTP Õ║ĢÕ▒éÕ«óµłĘń½»\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the HTTP underlying client layer for the AgentCube Python SDK (AR-029). It focuses on session management, connection pooling, timeout handling, header management, and error handling for both control plane and data plane communications.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-029\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK uses HTTP for communication with both the Workload Manager (control plane) and the Router (data plane). This AR defines the HTTP client layer that handles:\n- Session management with connection pooling\n- Timeout configuration (connect and read timeouts)\n- Header management (Authorization, session IDs, Content-Type)\n- Request/response handling for different operation types\n- Error handling and exception conversion\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-029-001: HTTP Session ńö¤ÕæĮÕæ©µ£¤ń«ĪńÉå\n\nThe system SHALL manage `requests.Session` lifecycle to ensure proper connection pooling and cleanup.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-001-A ŌĆö Session creation with connection pooling\n\n- **GIVEN** `create_session(pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10)` is called\n- **WHEN** the function executes\n- **THEN** it SHALL return a `requests.Session` with `HTTPAdapter` mounted for both `http://` and `https://` schemes\n- **AND** the adapter SHALL have `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-001-B ŌĆö Session context manager cleanup\n\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterClient` or `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** the `with` block exits normally\n- **THEN** the underlying `requests.Session` SHALL be closed via `.close()`\n- **AND** all HTTP connections SHALL be released back to the pool\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-001-C ŌĆö Session cleanup on exception\n\n- **GIVEN** an exception occurs within a context manager block\n- **WHEN** the `__exit__` method is called with exception info\n- **THEN** the session SHALL still be closed\n- **AND** the original exception SHALL be re-raised after cleanup\n\n---\n\n### AR-029-002: HTTP Ķ»Ęµ▒éĶČģµŚČĶĪīõĖ║\n\nThe system SHALL handle connect timeouts and read timeouts correctly for all HTTP operations.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-002-A ŌĆö Connect timeout applies to all requests\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized with `connect_timeout=5.0`\n- **WHEN** a request is made to an unreachable host\n- **THEN** a `requests.exceptions.ConnectTimeout` SHALL be raised within 5 seconds\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-002-B ŌĆö Read timeout for long-running operations\n\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with a command that takes longer than the read timeout\n- **WHEN** the server does not respond within `(connect_timeout + timeout)` seconds\n- **THEN** a `requests.exceptions.ReadTimeout` SHALL be raised\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-002-C ŌĆö Timeout tuple construction\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke` is called with default timeout settings\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the `timeout` parameter SHALL be a tuple `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `connect_timeout` defaults to `5.0` and `timeout` defaults to `120`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-002-D ŌĆö Per-call timeout override\n\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=300)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent\n- **THEN** the read timeout SHALL be `timeout + 2.0` seconds (302 seconds total) to allow for server-side timeout handling\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-002-E ŌĆö Default timeout values\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without timeout arguments\n- **WHEN** the client is created\n- **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120` and `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`\n\n---\n\n### AR-029-003: HTTP Õż┤ķā©ń«ĪńÉå\n\nThe system SHALL correctly set and manage HTTP headers for both control plane and data plane requests.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-003-A ŌĆö Authorization header on control plane\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized with a valid `auth_token`\n- **WHEN** `create_session` is called\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include header `Authorization: Bearer {auth_token}`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-003-B ŌĆö No Authorization header when token is empty\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without `auth_token`\n- **WHEN** a request is made\n- **THEN** the `Authorization` header SHALL NOT be included\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-003-C ŌĆö Session ID header for Code Interpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `session_id=\"test-session-123\"`\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` is called\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: test-session-123`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-003-D ŌĆö Session ID header for Agent Runtime\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is used\n- **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n- **THEN** the request SHALL include header defined by `SESSION_HEADER` constant (`x-agentcube-session-id`)\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-003-E ŌĆö Content-Type header for JSON requests\n\n- **GIVEN** `_request` is called with a JSON body\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the header `Content-Type: application/json` SHALL be set\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-003-F ŌĆö Multipart upload content-type\n\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is sent as multipart/form-data\n- **THEN** the outer request SHALL NOT have `Content-Type: application/json`\n- **AND** the `x-agentcube-session-id` header SHALL still be included\n\n---\n\n### AR-029-004: HTTP ķöÖĶ»»ÕżäńÉå\n\nThe system SHALL handle HTTP error responses appropriately and convert them to SDK-specific exceptions.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-004-A ŌĆö Non-200 response on create session\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session` receives HTTP 400 or 500\n- **WHEN** the response is not successful\n- **THEN** an appropriate `requests.exceptions.HTTPError` SHALL be raised\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-004-B ŌĆö 404 treated as success for delete\n\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session` is called with a non-existent `session_id`\n- **WHEN** the server returns HTTP 404\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True` (treating \"not found\" as successful deletion)\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-004-C ŌĆö Connection error handling\n\n- **GIVEN** the Router is unreachable\n- **WHEN** a data plane request is made\n- **THEN** a `requests.exceptions.ConnectionError` SHALL be raised\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-004-D ŌĆö Response JSON parsing failure\n\n- **GIVEN** the server returns non-JSON response\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` tries to parse the response as JSON\n- **THEN** a `JSONDecodeError` or equivalent SHALL be raised\n\n---\n\n### AR-029-005: Base URL Ķ¦Żµ×ÉõĖÄµ×äķĆĀ\n\nThe system SHALL correctly resolve and construct base URLs for both control plane and data plane.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-005-A ŌĆö Control plane URL from environment\n\n- **GIVEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable is set to `https://wm.example.com`\n- **AND** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without arguments\n- **WHEN** the client is used\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `https://wm.example.com`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-005-B ŌĆö Control plane URL from argument\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"https://custom-wm.example.com\")`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** argument SHALL take precedence over environment variable\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-005-C ŌĆö Data plane base URL from router\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `router_url`, `namespace`, and `cr_name`\n- **AND** `base_url` is NOT provided\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be constructed as `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-005-D ŌĆö Data plane base URL explicit override\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is initialized with explicit `base_url=\"https://custom.example.com/api\"`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be exactly `https://custom.example.com/api`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-005-E ŌĆö Agent Runtime base URL construction\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `router_url`, `namespace`, and `agent_name`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `self.base_url` SHALL be `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n\n---\n\n### AR-029-006: Ķ»Ęµ▒éõĮōµ×äķĆĀ\n\nThe system SHALL construct HTTP request bodies correctly for different operation types.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-006-A ŌĆö Execute command JSON body\n\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command` is called with `command=[\"echo\", \"hello\"]` and `timeout=60`\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the JSON body SHALL be `{\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello\"], \"timeout\": \"60s\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-006-B ŌĆö Write file base64 encoding\n\n- **GIVEN** `write_file` is called with `content=\"Hello World\"` and `remote_path=\"/tmp/test.txt\"`\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the JSON body SHALL include `{\"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"content\": \"<base64-encoded>\", \"mode\": \"0644\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-006-C ŌĆö Download file streaming\n\n- **GIVEN** `download_file` is called\n- **WHEN** the GET request is made to `api/files/{clean_path}`\n- **THEN** `stream=True` SHALL be set on the request\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-006-D ŌĆö List files query parameter\n\n- **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\"/tmp\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request is prepared\n- **THEN** the request SHALL be GET to `api/files` with query parameter `path=/tmp`\n\n---\n\n### AR-029-007: Token µ¢ćõ╗ČĶ»╗ÕÅ¢\n\nThe system SHALL handle token file reading gracefully with appropriate fallback behavior.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-007-A ŌĆö Token file exists and readable\n\n- **GIVEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` exists with content `eyJ...`\n- **AND** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without `auth_token`\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `self.token` SHALL be the file contents (stripped)\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-007-B ŌĆö Token file does not exist\n\n- **GIVEN** the service account token file does not exist\n- **AND** `ControlPlaneClient` is initialized without `auth_token`\n- **WHEN** `read_token_from_file` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL return an empty string `\"\"`\n- **AND** no exception SHALL be raised\n\n---\n\n### AR-029-008: µŚźÕ┐ŚĶ«░ÕĮĢ\n\nThe system SHALL log HTTP operations for debugging and monitoring purposes.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-008-A ŌĆö Logger creation with default level\n\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is created\n- **THEN** the default log level SHALL be `logging.INFO`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-008-B ŌĆö Custom logger level\n\n- **GIVEN** `get_logger(\"agentcube\", level=logging.DEBUG)` is called\n- **WHEN** the logger is configured\n- **THEN** the logger level SHALL be `logging.DEBUG`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-008-C ŌĆö Verbose mode enables debug logging\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(verbose=True)` is initialized\n- **WHEN** the client is created\n- **THEN** the logger SHALL be set to `DEBUG` level\n\n---\n\n### AR-029-009: Õ«óµłĘń½»ÕŁŚµ«ĄÕłØÕ¦ŗÕī¢\n\nThe system SHALL correctly initialize all client fields as documented.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-009-A ŌĆö CodeInterpreterClient fields\n\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient(name=\"test\", namespace=\"ns\", ttl=1800, verbose=True, session_id=\"sess-1\")`\n- **WHEN** the client is initialized\n- **THEN** the instance SHALL have fields: `name=\"test\"`, `namespace=\"ns\"`, `ttl=1800`, `verbose=True`, `session_id=\"sess-1\"`, `cp_client`, `dp_client`, `router_url`, `logger`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-009-B ŌĆö AgentRuntimeClient fields\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"agent1\", namespace=\"default\", timeout=60, connect_timeout=3.0)`\n- **WHEN** the client is initialized\n- **THEN** the instance SHALL have fields: `agent_name=\"agent1\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `timeout=60`, `connect_timeout=3.0`, `router_url`, `session_id`, `dp_client`, `logger`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-009-C ŌĆö ControlPlaneClient defaults\n\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient()` is initialized with no arguments\n- **WHEN** the client is created\n- **THEN** `self.timeout` SHALL be `120`, `self.connect_timeout` SHALL be `5.0`, `self.pool_connections` SHALL be `10`, `self.pool_maxsize` SHALL be `10`\n\n---\n\n### AR-029-010: Õ╝éÕĖĖń▒╗Õ▒éµ¼Īń╗ōµ×ä\n\nThe system SHALL provide a clear exception hierarchy for different error conditions.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-010-A ŌĆö AgentCubeError is base class\n\n- **GIVEN** `AgentCubeError` is the base exception\n- **WHEN** any SDK-specific exception is raised\n- **THEN** it SHALL be a subclass of `AgentCubeError`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-010-B ŌĆö CommandExecutionError attributes\n\n- **GIVEN** `CommandExecutionError` is raised for a failed command\n- **WHEN** the exception is caught\n- **THEN** it SHALL have `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command` attributes\n- **AND** the exception message SHALL include the exit code and stderr\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-010-C ŌĆö SessionError definition exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `SessionError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n- **WHEN** the module is imported\n- **THEN** `SessionError` SHALL be available as `AgentCubeError` subclass\n\n#### Scenario: AR-029-010-D ŌĆö DataPlaneError definition exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `DataPlaneError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n- **WHEN** the module is imported\n- **THEN** `DataPlaneError` SHALL be available as `AgentCubeError` subclass\n\n---\n\n## Non-Requirements\n\nThe following are explicitly out of scope for this AR:\n\n- Authentication logic beyond token file reading and Bearer token header setting\n- TLS/SSL certificate validation configuration (use requests defaults)\n- Retry logic for transient failures\n- Request/response logging at HTTP wire level\n- Custom HTTP adapter implementations beyond connection pooling\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Description |\n|------------|-------------|\n| AR-028 | AgentRuntimeClient implementation |\n| python-sdk/design.md | Base SDK design document |\n| python-sdk/spec.md | Base specification |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Criterion | Verification Method |\n|----|-----------|---------------------|\n| AC001 | `create_session` returns Session with HTTPAdapter for http/https | Unit test verifying adapter mount |\n| AC002 | Context manager closes session on exit | Integration test with mock server |\n| AC003 | Connect timeout raises ConnectTimeout | Test against unreachable host |\n| AC029-004 | Read timeout raises ReadTimeout | Test with slow server response |\n| AC005 | Authorization header set when token provided | Mock server assertion |\n| AC006 | Session ID header sent on data plane requests | Request inspection test |\n| AC007 | 404 on delete returns True | Unit test with mock response |\n| AC008 | Base URL constructed correctly from router | Path construction verification |\n| AC009 | Request body format matches specification | JSON structure validation |\n| AC010 | Token file fallback returns empty string | Test with missing file |\n| AC011 | Logger respects verbose flag | Level inspection test |\n| AC012 | Exception hierarchy correct | Import and inheritance test |\n\n---\n\n## Test Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n- Test `create_session` returns properly configured Session\n- Test timeout tuple construction\n- Test header construction for different request types\n- Test URL construction for control plane and data plane\n- Test token file reading (with and without file)\n- Test exception class hierarchy\n\n### Integration Tests\n- Test context manager cleanup\n- Test actual HTTP requests with mock server\n- Test timeout behavior with slow responses\n- Test error handling for various HTTP status codes\n\n### Mock Server Tests\n- Use `responses` or `requests-mock` to simulate HTTP responses\n- Verify request headers, bodies, and path construction\n- Test edge cases like 404 on delete\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Key Components\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| `create_session` | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | Creates requests.Session with HTTPAdapter |\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | HTTP client for Workload Manager |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | HTTP client for Code Interpreter Router |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | HTTP client for Agent Runtime Router |\n| `read_token_from_file` | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | Reads service account token |\n| `get_logger` | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | Creates configured logger |\n| Exception classes | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception hierarchy |\n\n### Configuration Defaults\n\n| Parameter | Default | Applied To |\n|-----------|---------|------------|\n| timeout | 120 | All HTTP clients |\n| connect_timeout | 5.0 | All HTTP clients |\n| pool_connections | 10 | Session adapter |\n| pool_maxsize | 10 | Session adapter |\n\n### Header Constants\n\n| Header | Value | Usage |\n|--------|-------|-------|\n| Session ID | `x-agentcube-session-id` | Code Interpreter & Agent Runtime |\n| Authorization | `Bearer {token}` | Control plane (when token provided) |\n| Content-Type | `application/json` | JSON request bodies |","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775870423911,"end":1775870423933}}}}
